metadata.name: Fading Lines
metadata.description:
The world changes, and so do our cities. While in 1913 the tallest building in New York City was 241 m, this number is currently more than double that (541 m). This height belongs to the One World Trade Center, which can be seen in the bottom left corner of the photograph. A spectacular building whose mirroring surface disappears high into the sky. This special edition 1 of 10 item is for those who admire abstract images, where little is seen at first glance, but lots to uncover when looking closely.

Location: One World Trade Center, New York City, The United States
